cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.MM 

This paper deals with the problem of salient object detection using deep learning techniques, which is a popular topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper proposes a novel approach that considers relative rank of salient objects, which involves a hierarchical representation and stage-wise refinement, indicating the use of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) techniques. The paper also mentions the use of neural networks (cs.NE) and metrics for measuring success in salient object detection, which are common topics in multimedia (cs.MM) research.
